{"parse":{"title":"living","pageid":8393,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈlɪvɪŋ/}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-living.wav|a=UK}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-living.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɪvɪŋ|s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|livynge}}, {{m|enm|libbyng}}, {{m|enm|livinde}}, {{m|enm|livand}}, {{m|enm|livende}}, {{m|enm|libbinde}}, {{m|enm|libbende}}, from {{inh|en|ang|lifiġende}}, {{m|ang|lifiende}}, {{m|ang|libbende}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*libbjan|*libbjandī}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*libjaną|*libjandz|t=living}}, present participle of {{der|en|gem-pro|*libjaną|t=to live}}, equivalent to {{suf|en|live|-ing|id2=participial}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|libbend|t=living}}, {{cog|nl|levend|t=living}}, {{cog|de|lebend|t=living}}, {{cog|sv|levande|t=living}}, {{cog|is|lifandi|t=living}}.\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|en|verb form}}\n\n# {{present participle of|en|live}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj|-}}\n\n# Having [[life]]; [[alive]].\n#: {{ux|en|a '''living''', breathing child}}\n#: {{ux|en|Respect for the dead does not preclude respect for the '''living'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Schuster Hepaticae|volume=V|page=ix|text=It is also pertinent to note that the current obvious decline in work on holarctic hepatics most surely reflects a current obsession with cataloging and with nomenclature of the organisms—as divorced from their study as '''living''' entities.}}\n# In use or [[exist]]ing.\n#: {{ux|en|Hunanese is a '''living''' language.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1897|author=Richard Marsh|title=The Beetle\n|passage=The cab pulled up in front of a tumbledown cheap ‘villa’ in an unfinished cheap neighbourhood, — the whole place a '''living''' monument of the defeat of the speculative builder.}}\n# [[true to life|True to life]].\n#: {{ux|en|This is the '''living''' image of Fidel Castro.}}\n# Of rock or stone, existing in its original state and place.\n#* {{RQ:Haggard She|passage=This we followed for about five paces, when it suddenly widened out into a small chamber, about eight feet square, and hewn out of the '''living''' rock.}}\n# Continually updated; not [[static]]\n#: {{ux|en|HTML is a '''living''' standard.}}\n# {{non-gloss|Used as an [[intensifier]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|He almost beat the '''living''' daylights out of me.}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|having life}} {{l|en|extant}}, {{l|en|living}}, {{l|en|vital}}; see also [[Thesaurus:alive]]\n* {{sense|existing}} {{l|en|extant}}; See also [[Thesaurus:existent]]\n* {{sense|representing life}} {{l|en|lifey}}, {{l|en|lifelike}}, {{l|en|limned}}, {{l|en|lively}}, {{l|en|naturalistic}}\n* {{sense|intensifier}} {{l|en|blasted}}, {{l|en|doggone}}, {{l|en|stinking}}; see also [[Thesaurus:damned]]\n\n=====Antonyms=====\n* {{l|en|dead}}\n* {{l|en|nonliving}}\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n* {{l|en|long-living}}\n* {{l|en|longest-living}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|living death|not a living soul|living end|living space|living floor|sliving|livingly|everliving|landliving|livingness|livingry|unliving|living room|high-living|living diaper|living donation|living donor|living thing|living internet theory|living memory|living will|activities of daily living|by the living jingo|clean-living|free-living|in living color|in living memory|knock the living daylights out of|living bandage|living constitution|living dead|living fossil|living hell|living hinge|living impaired|living language|living legend|living mulch|living museum|living picture|living proof|living rock|living sculpture|living statue|living street|living tissue|living tree doctrine|living wall|non-living|scare the living daylights out of|within living memory|living newspaper|living wage|living stone|living shield|living trust|living fence}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|en|live}}, {{l|en|life}}\n* {{l|en|alive}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|having life}}\n* Albanian: {{t|sq|rron}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|حَيّ|m|tr=ḥayy}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|կենդանի}}, {{qualifier|colloquial, dialectal}} {{t+|hy|սաղ}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|diri}}, {{t+|az|sağ}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|тере}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|জীবন্ত}}, {{t+|bn|জিন্দা}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|жив}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|viu}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|vivanta}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|elävä}}, {{t+|fi|elollinen}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|vivant}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|vivo}}\n* German: {{t+|de|lebend}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ζωντανός}}, {{t+|el|έμβιος}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ζωός}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|חי|tr=khay}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|जीवित}}, {{t|hi|ज़िंदा}}, {{t+|hi|जीवी}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|lifandi}}\n* Kabuverdianu: {{t|kea|bibu}}, {{t|kea|vive}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|살다|alt=산}}, {{t+|ko|살다|alt=살아 있는}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|animalis}}, {{t+|la|vivus}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|kaiao}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|जिवंत}}, {{t|mr|सजीव}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|żywy}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|vivo}}, {{t+|pt|vivente}}\n* Rapa Nui: {{t|rap|aringa}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|viu|m}}, {{t+|ro|vie|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|живо́й}}, {{t+|ru|жить|alt=живу́щий}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|आयु}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|живети}}, {{t|sh|живјети}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|živeti}}, {{t+|sh|živjeti}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|žywy}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|levande}}\n* Tocharian B: {{t|txb|śāmane}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|живи́й}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|in use or existing}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|ka}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|жив}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|elävä}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|vivo|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|lebend}}, {{t+|de|existent}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ζωντανός}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|קַיָּם|m}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|현존하다|alt=현존하는}}, {{t|ko|현존|alt=현존의}}, {{t+|ko|현대|alt=현대의}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|żywy}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|vivo}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|жить|alt=живу́щий}}, {{t+|ru|живо́й}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t|sh|živuća}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|žywy}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|levande}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|of everyday life}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|生活}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|levens-}}\n* Finnish: {{qualifier|in compounds}} {{t+|fi|elin-}}\n* German: {{t|de|Lebens-}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|생활|alt=생활의}}, {{t|ko|거주|alt=거주의}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|życiowy}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|жи́зненный}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t|sh|živući}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|true to life}}\n* Albanian: {{t|sq|përjetuar}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|тормошсан}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|elävä}}\n* German: {{t+|de|lebensecht}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|실물|alt=실물 그대로의}}, {{t+|ko|생생하다|alt=생생한}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|жива}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|živa}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|levande}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|used as an intensifier}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|정말}}, {{t+|ko|정말로}}, {{t+|ko|진짜}}, {{t|ko|진짜로}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|vive}}, {{t-check|ia|vivente}}\n* Romanian: {{t+check|ro|viu}}\n* Spanish: {{t+check|es|vivo}}, {{t+check|es|viviente}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|livynge}}, {{m|enm|libbynge}}, equivalent to {{suf|en|live|-ing|id2=gerund noun}}. Cognate with {{cog|dum|levinge}}, (whence {{cog|nl|leving|t=way of life, living}}), {{cog|gml|lēvinge|t=living}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The state of being [[alive]].\n# Financial means; a means of maintaining life; [[livelihood]]\n#: {{collocation|en|it's a '''living'''}}\n#: {{ux|en|What do you do for a '''living'''?}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=10 Dec 83|volume=11|number=21|journal=Gay Community News|page=14|author=Jolanta Benal|title=The Second Revolution|text=Career opportunity {{...}} is the one who never knocks — especially not on the doors of women, who are still hooking, housewifing and hairdressing for their '''livings'''.}}\n# A style of life.\n#: {{ux|en|plain '''living'''}}\n#: {{ux|en|The National Brewing Company declared that the Chesapeake Bay region was the Land of Pleasant '''Living'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|with \"the\"}} Those who are alive: [[#Adjective|living]] people.\n#: {{syn|en|q=archaic|quick#Noun}}\n#: {{ant|en|dead#Noun|;|q2=polite|deceased#Noun|departed#Noun}}\n#: {{collocation|en|in the land of '''the living'''}}\n#: {{collocation|en|Glad to see you're still among '''the living'''! [good-humored greeting]}}\n#: {{ux|en|Some say that the spirits of the departed walk among '''the living''', though most of us do not see them.}}\n# {{lb|en|canon law}} A position in a church (usually the Church of England) that has attached to it a source of income; an ecclesiastical [[benefice]].\n#* {{RQ:Spelman De Non Temerandis Ecclesiis|pages=2–3|pageref=2|passage=A Rectory or Parſonage, is a ''Spirituall '''liuing''''', compoſed of ''Land'', ''Tythe'', and other ''Oblations'' of the people, ſeparate or dedicate to God in any ''Congregation'', for the ſeruice of his Church there, and for the maintenance of the ''Gouernour'' or ''Miniſter'' thereof, to vvhoſe charge the ſame is committed.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2015|author=GR Evans|title=Edward Hicks: Pacifist Bishop at War|passage=The patron of the '''living''' who had the right to nominate a particular priest might make the choice, but the '''living''' was actually granted by the local bishop.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|en|it takes a heap of living to make a house a home|cost of living|earn a living|it takes a lot of living to make a house a home|land of the living|living chamber|living conditions|living history|living quarters|living standard|living wage|scratch a living|simple living|standard of living\n|make a living|assisted living|sober living house|the world owes one a living\n|coliving|livingless|misliving|what do you do for a living}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|state of being alive}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|yaşayış}}, {{t+|az|həyat}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|живе́ене|n}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|vivado}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|elo}}, {{t+|fi|eläminen}}, {{t+|fi|elämä}}\n* German: {{t|de|Lebende|f}}, {{t|de|Lebender|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ζωή|f}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|जीवित}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|생존(生存)}}, {{t+|ko|살다|alt=살아 있음}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|iiná}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|życie}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|жизнь|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|liv|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|financial means; a means of maintaining life}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|مَعِيشَة|f}}, {{t|ar|مَعَاش|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|прехра́на|f}}, {{t+|bg|препита́ние|n}}, {{t|bg|[[средство|средства]] за [[преживя́ване]]|n-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|生計|tr=shēngjì}}, {{t+|cmn|飯碗|tr=fànwǎn}} {{qualifier|lit.: \"rice bowl\"}}\n* Finnish: {{qualifier|in compounds}} {{t|fi|ansio-}}, {{t+|fi|työ}}, {{t+|fi|elinkeino}}, {{t+|fi|elanto}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Lebensunterhalt|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|επιούσιος|m}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מִחְיָה|f|tr=miẖyá}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|जीविका|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|生計|tr=せいけい, seikei}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|생계(生計)}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|victus|m}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|levebrød|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|levebrød|n}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|życie}}, {{t+|pl|utrzymanie|n}}, {{t|pl|źródło utrzymania|n}}, {{t|pl|środki do życia|m-p}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|сре́дства к существова́нию|n-p}}, {{t+|ru|пропита́ние|n}}, {{t+|ru|жизнь|f}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|ealáhus}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|ganarse la vida}}, {{t+|es|trabajo|m}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|פּרנסה|f|tr=parnose}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|style of life}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|حَيَاة|f}}, {{t|ar|طَرِيقَة فِي حَيَاة|f|tr=ṭarīqa fī ḥayāh}}, {{t|ar|نَمَط حَيَاة|m}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|yaşayış}}, {{t+|az|həyat}}, {{t|az|yaşayış tərzi}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|на́чин на живо́т|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|生活方式|tr=shēnghuó fāngshì}}, {{t+|cmn|生態|tr=shēngtài}}, {{t+|cmn|方式|tr=fāngshì}}, {{t+|cmn|生活|tr=shēnghuó}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|elämä}}, {{t+|fi|elintapa}}, {{t+|fi|elo}}, {{t+|fi|elämäntapa}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|mode de vie|f}}, {{t+|fr|vie|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Leben|n}}, {{t+|de|Lebensumstände|f}}, {{t+|de|Lebensweise|f}}, {{t+|de|Lebensstil|m}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|जीवनशैली|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|生活様式|tr=せいかつようしき, seikatsu yōshiki}}, {{t+|ja|暮らし|tr=くらし, kurashi}}, {{t+|ja|生活|tr=せいかつ, seikatsu}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|생활방식(生活方式)}}, {{t+|ko|생활양식(生活樣式)}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|życie}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|о́браз жи́зни|m}}, {{t+|ru|стиль жи́зни|m}}, {{t+|ru|жизнь|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|estilo de vida|m}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|pamumuhay}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|those who are alive}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|живите|p}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|superī|m-p}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|(canon law) a position in a church attached to a source of income}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{cln|en|intensifiers}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|fr|living}} or, less plausibly, an independent truncated borrowing from {{bor|nl|en|living room}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈlɪ.vɪŋ/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-living.ogg}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|ɪvɪŋ|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|li|ving}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-s|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|Belgium}} [[living room]]\n#: {{syn|nl|huiskamer|woonkamer}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:living room<alt:living (room)>}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|living room|living (room)}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-living.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[living room]]\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n{{C|fr|Rooms}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{pseudo-loan|it|en}}, a clipping of {{der|it|en|living room}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m}}\n\n# [[living room]]\n#: {{syn|it|soggiorno}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ro|en|living-room}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|n|livinguri}}\n\n# [[living room]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-n-uri}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|living room|living (room)}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|livin}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|es|Rioplatense|Chile}} [[living room]]\n#: {{syn|es|sala de estar}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n* {{R:es:DA}}\n\n{{C|es|Rooms}}"}}